2 HOUSE BILL 1063
1 (a) The Commission shall provide an opportunity for a hearing before proceeding
2 with the design or construction of a water supply or sanitary sewer system.
3 (b) Subject to subsection (c) of this section, the Commission:
4 (1) shall advertise in newspapers and technical media that the Commission
5 considers appropriate for bids or proposals for design or construction services for any part
6 of a water supply or sanitary sewer system; and
7 (2) may readvertise any part of the services needed if the Commission
8 considers the prices quoted in response to a prior advertisement to be unreasonable.
9 (c) (1) Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, the Commission may use
10 day labor to complete any part of the design or construction of a water supply or sanitary
11 sewer system.
12 (2) Notwithstanding § 20–105(a) of this subtitle, the Commission may
13 spend up to $15,000 for day labor for any part of construction services without advertising
14 for or receiving bids or proposals.
15 (d) (1) Except as provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection, the Commission
16 may enter into any type of contract under this subtitle that promotes the best interest of
17 the Commission.
18 (2) The Commission:
19 (i) may not enter a cost–plus–percentage–of–cost contract; and
20 (ii) shall prohibit a cost–plus–percentage–of–cost subcontract under
21 a contract with the Commission.
22 (e) [The Commission may only enter into a design/build contract for a facilities
23 construction contract with costs exceeding $2,000,000.
24 (f)] The Commission may reject any bid or proposal.
25 [(g)] (F) (1) The Commission may require a contract to be secured by bonds,
26 penalties, and conditions.
27 (2) Security authorized under this subsection is enforceable in any court of
28 competent jurisdiction.
29 [(h)] (G) The Commission:
30 (1) may adopt regulations to establish:

HOUSE BILL 1063 3
1 (I) a prequalification process for bidders or offerors; and
2 (II) ALTERNATIVE PROJECT DELIVERY AND SOLICITATION
3 METHODS THAT PROMOTE THE BEST INTERESTS OF THE COMMISSION; AND
4 (2) shall adopt regulations to govern discussions held with offerors under §
5 20–105(c)(3) of this subtitle.
6 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
7 October 1, 2025.
